01:37:56.083 --> 01:37:58.244
He's gambling.

01:38:00.054 --> 01:38:02.113
- Yep.
- Yeah.

01:38:03.090 --> 01:38:06.253
I just can't believe I'm here again.

01:38:06.327 --> 01:38:08.557
I just...

01:38:08.629 --> 01:38:11.826
I just can't believe it, you know.
I saw it coming.

01:38:11.899 --> 01:38:14.424
I just couldn't stop it.

01:38:20.107 --> 01:38:22.667
I gotta win one more game.

01:38:23.644 --> 01:38:26.010
You can't fix this, Brandon.

01:38:27.081 --> 01:38:29.345
You can't fix it.

01:38:57.345 --> 01:39:00.041
- Come here for a second.
- What?

01:39:00.815 --> 01:39:05.081
I'm gonna kiss you right now, OK?
Trust me on this.

01:39:33.814 --> 01:39:36.408
(Julia) OK, Daddy, open the present.

01:39:40.488 --> 01:39:42.285
Oh!

01:39:42.356 --> 01:39:46.622
Oh, look at this. It's so beautiful.

01:39:46.694 --> 01:39:49.686
Daddy, not the paper! In there.

01:39:50.164 --> 01:39:52.632
Oh!

01:39:52.700 --> 01:39:55.328
Oh, man.

01:39:55.403 --> 01:39:56.995
Beautiful.

01:39:57.071 --> 01:39:59.369
Baby, this is beautiful.

01:39:59.807 --> 01:40:01.707
- Happy anniversary.
- (knock at door)

01:40:02.143 --> 01:40:04.611
- I'll get it.
- OK.

01:40:04.679 --> 01:40:08.012
Oh, thank you, honey.
What am I gonna do with this?

01:40:09.183 --> 01:40:11.674
- It's a dangerous thing to give me.
- Brandon!

01:40:11.752 --> 01:40:13.913
- (Brandon) Hello.
- Look who's here.

01:40:13.988 --> 01:40:17.287
- Oh, you're back from Vegas.
- (Walter) Join the celebration.

01:40:17.358 --> 01:40:19.622
- What's going on?
- Well...

01:40:19.694 --> 01:40:23.186
Toni and I were married
12 years ago today.

01:40:23.264 --> 01:40:25.562
- Congratulations.
- Thanks.

01:40:25.633 --> 01:40:28.727
Angel, give Mommy her gift.

01:40:29.637 --> 01:40:33.164
(Walter hums "Funeral March" by Chopin)

01:40:36.510 --> 01:40:39.070
It's OK, baby. I saved for it.

01:40:39.146 --> 01:40:41.774
We got enough, believe me.

01:40:43.551 --> 01:40:46.076
We're not broke yet, honey. Put 'em on.

01:40:46.520 --> 01:40:50.320
Come on. I wanna see them on you.
Let me see them.

01:40:50.758 --> 01:40:52.851
Ooh!

01:40:52.927 --> 01:40:56.385
I got beautiful taste, don't I?
Brandon, I couldn't leave you out.

01:40:56.464 --> 01:41:00.195
It's sort of our anniversary,
anyway, isn't it?

01:41:01.502 --> 01:41:03.595
They're made for car racing.

01:41:03.671 --> 01:41:08.438
The guy who wore this
won six straight times at Le Mans.

01:41:08.509 --> 01:41:11.000
Put it on.
Maybe you'll start winning again.

01:41:11.078 --> 01:41:13.273
Walter, I can't take this, man.

01:41:14.849 --> 01:41:17.443
- Why not?
- It's too much.

01:41:17.518 --> 01:41:20.976
We all love each other here, right?
You're family.

01:41:21.055 --> 01:41:24.183
I'm like your father, you're like my son.

01:41:24.825 --> 01:41:28.283
That would make you his mother,
wouldn't it, Toni?

01:41:30.030 --> 01:41:33.056
Oh, I said something wrong, didn't I?

01:41:33.134 --> 01:41:36.103
What are you doing? Keep 'em on.

01:41:37.004 --> 01:41:41.532
- They're for evening, Walter.
- So what? Wear 'em to bed. Come on.

01:41:41.609 --> 01:41:43.975
Brandon, I got you.

01:41:44.044 --> 01:41:45.841
Who do you like in the big game?

01:41:45.913 --> 01:41:49.314
- Turn that off, Walter.
- Why? What, are you camera shy?

01:41:49.383 --> 01:41:52.409
- Turn that off.
- Hey, man, surprise me.

01:41:52.486 --> 01:41:54.647
We'll break it
when we do the live TV show.

01:42:12.173 --> 01:42:17.042
(man) Coming up on "Sports Advisors,"
John Anthony's Super Forty selections.

01:42:17.111 --> 01:42:20.274
It's live, and it's next.

01:42:20.881 --> 01:42:24.373
I know he's supposed to be here.
I know where he is. He's in the bathroom.

01:42:24.452 --> 01:42:26.443
(breathes heavily)

01:42:29.957 --> 01:42:31.720
Fuck!

01:42:31.792 --> 01:42:35.922
- (knock at door)
- (man) Two minutes till we go live.

01:42:36.931 --> 01:42:38.023
(vomits)

01:42:38.466 --> 01:42:40.559
What the hell is he doing?

01:42:55.082 --> 01:42:57.312
Heads, New York, tails, Kansas City.

01:42:59.753 --> 01:43:01.914
Heads, over, tails, under.

01:43:03.424 --> 01:43:05.289
John Anthony!

01:43:12.566 --> 01:43:15.501
- Here he is.
- (director) 40 seconds till we're live.

01:43:15.569 --> 01:43:18.265
40 seconds.
Come on, come on, come on.

01:43:23.210 --> 01:43:26.737
- (director) We're at 30.
- Uh, New York, minus one and a half

01:43:26.814 --> 01:43:28.975
and the over, 36.

01:43:29.750 --> 01:43:32.014
Wanna know about those picks?

01:43:32.086 --> 01:43:34.782
- (director) 20 seconds to air.
- Hold on.

01:43:34.855 --> 01:43:37.255
What should I know about 'em?

01:43:37.324 --> 01:43:39.815
I flipped a coin to decide.

01:43:42.396 --> 01:43:45.763
- (director) Ten.
- Push it all the way, Southie.

01:43:47.735 --> 01:43:50.169
And five, four,

01:43:50.237 --> 01:43:52.637
three, two...

01:43:52.706 --> 01:43:57.006
(man) Live from the WDIX studios
high above Manhattan,

01:43:57.077 --> 01:43:59.307
here's your host, Walter Abrams.

01:43:59.380 --> 01:44:02.713
Hello, everybody,
and welcome to the big weekend.

01:44:03.183 --> 01:44:07.847
Never before in the history of this industry
has an offer been made

01:44:07.922 --> 01:44:10.482
like the one I'm about to present
to you now.

01:44:10.558 --> 01:44:15.325
I am so confident
in John Anthony's picks for this Sunday,

01:44:15.396 --> 01:44:20.095
I'm so sure of the skills
he's brought to bear,

01:44:20.167 --> 01:44:23.000
and so anxious for you
to get on the phone

01:44:23.070 --> 01:44:25.698
and dial the toll-free number
on your screen

01:44:25.773 --> 01:44:29.766
that for the first time
in sports-service history,

01:44:29.843 --> 01:44:33.643
I am going to guarantee our picks
this weekend.

01:44:34.415 --> 01:44:38.875
- What's that mean?
- What does that mean? It means this.

01:44:38.953 --> 01:44:43.185
You tell us how much you're betting
with your bookie,

01:44:43.257 --> 01:44:46.226
you lose, we cover.

01:44:47.294 --> 01:44:50.457
You heard me right. That's risk-free.

01:44:50.531 --> 01:44:53.159
Now let's go to the oracle,

01:44:53.233 --> 01:44:55.360
God's gift, John Anthony.

01:44:55.436 --> 01:44:58.963
Wow. That's all I can say.

01:44:59.039 --> 01:45:03.476
The phones are gonna be flooded, Walter,
and they should be.

01:45:03.544 --> 01:45:08.140
Hey, John, why don't you run down
the pitfalls facing the average bettor?

01:45:08.215 --> 01:45:13.482
I mean, when you think about it, a game
this huge, all the added dynamics...

01:45:13.554 --> 01:45:16.250
I mean, uh, without your expertise,

01:45:16.323 --> 01:45:21.158
I guess the average bettor might as well
just, what, flip a coin.

01:45:21.228 --> 01:45:25.358
Walter? No, no, no, no,
no, no, no, no, no, no, no.

01:45:25.432 --> 01:45:30.631
Hang on. You can't guarantee that they're gonna win.
That's insane. Come on.

01:45:30.704 --> 01:45:35.573
I say if you can flip a coin to make a pick,
I can guarantee the game.

01:45:35.643 --> 01:45:39.340
- What if we lose?
- Ah, fuck it. I'm ruined anyway.

01:45:39.413 --> 01:45:43.873
Look, man. Cover your ass, all right.
At least cap the thing out, right?

01:45:43.951 --> 01:45:47.387
- Oh, Brandon, can't you feel it?
- What?

01:45:47.454 --> 01:45:51.220
- Can't you just feel it?
- I have no idea what you're talking about.

01:45:51.291 --> 01:45:54.590
Oh, I think you do. I think you do.

01:45:54.662 --> 01:45:58.154
You know, the best part of the best drug
in the world ain't the high.

01:45:58.232 --> 01:46:01.292
It's the moment just before you take it.

01:46:01.368 --> 01:46:03.598
The dice are dancing on the table.

01:46:04.605 --> 01:46:07.301
Between now and the time they stop,

01:46:08.308 --> 01:46:10.776
that's the greatest high in the world.

01:46:11.612 --> 01:46:15.742
(Southie) Made up your mind yet?
It's the last minute! I'm here to make you money!

01:46:15.816 --> 01:46:19.217
New York's the one-and-a-half point
favorite, the over and under is 36.

01:46:19.286 --> 01:46:21.447
I want you to bet New York in the over.

01:46:21.522 --> 01:46:24.582
- Come on, guy, it's a fucking lock.
- It's New York in the over.

01:46:24.658 --> 01:46:28.526
You can parlay it, tease it,
do whatever you want, 'cause it's guaranteed.

01:46:28.595 --> 01:46:30.927
- Our reputation is the guarantee.
- (man) Tammy!

01:46:30.998 --> 01:46:32.158
(Tammy) I'm coming.

01:46:32.232 --> 01:46:35.201
28 years in the business,
we're not going anywhere.

01:46:35.269 --> 01:46:40.070
- Can we please get some air in here?
- (man) You gotta make up your mind.

01:46:40.140 --> 01:46:43.075
OK, that's it. Kill the phones. Come on.

01:46:43.143 --> 01:46:45.543
Right now. Let's go, let's go.

01:46:45.612 --> 01:46:48.445
(TV) They come from New York
and Kansas City in this match-up.

01:46:48.515 --> 01:46:51.040
The opening kickoff is coming up next.

01:46:58.192 --> 01:47:02.652
We are under way in Super Forty. It's
a high end-over-ender. Down the middle.

01:47:02.730 --> 01:47:06.689
Jackson gets it, a short one for the 15,
tries to angle over to the right side,

01:47:06.767 --> 01:47:09.235
stripped away from...

01:47:09.937 --> 01:47:12.269
- Kansas City comes up with it.
- Ah, man.

01:47:12.339 --> 01:47:17.299
Harris getting to the outside, turns,
clear path. Boy, does he have blocking.

01:47:17.377 --> 01:47:19.709
- Touchdown, Kansas City.
- Shit.

01:47:19.780 --> 01:47:23.113
- Sets out for the pocket. Simpson.
- He's open.

01:47:23.183 --> 01:47:27.142
Guns one over the middle, Simpson
on the completion. It's second and 15.

01:47:27.221 --> 01:47:29.451
- Setting up, he's got time again.
- Go, go.

01:47:29.523 --> 01:47:32.048
Looks down field
and the slam intercepted.

01:47:32.126 --> 01:47:34.924
- What the fuck is that?
- Dawkins finds a wave of blockers.

01:47:34.995 --> 01:47:40.365
Over to the near side, he's going to go
the distance. Touchdown, Kansas City.

01:47:40.434 --> 01:47:43.403
14-nothing, Kansas City over New York.

01:47:45.038 --> 01:47:48.201
New York's got it now
for the third time in the game.

01:47:48.275 --> 01:47:51.472
Back to throw once again,
pocket collapses and down it goes.

01:47:51.545 --> 01:47:55.413
Oh, man. You better hold on
to that coin you flipped,

01:47:55.482 --> 01:47:59.578
because this game keeps up like this,
I'm gonna have to borrow it.

01:47:59.653 --> 01:48:02.588
Well, it's not over yet, Walter.

01:48:02.656 --> 01:48:04.715
I wouldn't change my bet. Hm?

01:48:08.562 --> 01:48:10.996
And second and long,
second and about a dozen.

01:48:11.064 --> 01:48:13.658
Can they get something started?

01:48:16.403 --> 01:48:19.634
What are they counting on today?
Do they have to get away

01:48:19.706 --> 01:48:22.197
from the balanced attack
we've seen all season?

01:48:22.276 --> 01:48:26.975
Will they lose the ground game now?
Will they go over to the pass?

01:48:27.047 --> 01:48:32.246
Well, there is no way they'll be able
to run when they're 14 points down.

01:48:44.898 --> 01:48:49.358
Handoff goes to the second man through.
It's Jones, fullback, off the right side.

01:48:49.436 --> 01:48:52.371
He's got room, downfield he goes.
Will anybody catch him?

01:48:52.439 --> 01:48:55.670
Deep into the secondary now.
Touchdown, New York.

01:48:56.743 --> 01:49:00.611
Extra point makes it 14-7, Kansas City.

01:49:01.882 --> 01:49:07.286
(radio) Kansas scores on the eight-play
drive, capped with Rogers's 32-yard run.

01:49:07.354 --> 01:49:13.452
And that's the end of the third quarter.
It's Kansas City, 21, New York, ten.

01:49:13.527 --> 01:49:16.758
(TV) Back to throw once again.
Post available...

01:49:16.830 --> 01:49:19.765
- Let's go!
...beats the safety down the right side.

01:49:19.833 --> 01:49:21.824
He's in!

01:49:21.902 --> 01:49:23.767
All right!

01:49:23.837 --> 01:49:29.469
It's Kansas City, 21, New York, 17. What
a final four minutes we're going to have.

01:49:29.543 --> 01:49:31.204
- Where's Brandon?
- I don't know.

01:49:31.278 --> 01:49:33.269
Where's Brandon?

01:49:34.481 --> 01:49:36.972
We're back in it, babe!

01:49:37.050 --> 01:49:40.213
New York touchdown
and we win both bets!

01:49:41.288 --> 01:49:43.051
Hey!

01:49:43.123 --> 01:49:46.251
- Hey, Brandon?
- I believe this'll be their final possession.

01:49:46.326 --> 01:49:50.194
Can they do it? Can they get it done
like they have all year long?

01:49:50.264 --> 01:49:55.133
They're trailing by four. Don't forget,
the new rule doesn't apply here.

01:49:55.202 --> 01:49:57.762
They've gotta get into the end zone.

01:49:58.705 --> 01:50:01.606
- He left.
- I know.

01:50:01.675 --> 01:50:03.870
You didn't tell me?

01:50:08.015 --> 01:50:09.880
How about that?

01:50:09.950 --> 01:50:13.147
No goodbye, no... no nothing.

01:50:13.220 --> 01:50:17.452
- I'm sure it's all there in the letter.
- I'm sure it is.

01:50:17.591 --> 01:50:20.788
I wonder what's not in here.

01:50:20.861 --> 01:50:23.352
What do you mean?

01:50:23.931 --> 01:50:29.233
- What do you mean, what do I mean?
- He had enough. He wanted his life back.

01:50:29.303 --> 01:50:31.294
He said that to you?

01:50:31.371 --> 01:50:34.272
Well, loud and clear, by leaving.

01:50:35.876 --> 01:50:39.676
- I think it was something else.
- Yeah? Tell me.

01:50:40.447 --> 01:50:42.574
You know.

01:50:43.183 --> 01:50:44.650
No.

01:50:44.718 --> 01:50:47.380
You have no idea?

01:50:49.423 --> 01:50:53.416
- You're missing the game, Walter.
- Oh, no. This is the game.

01:50:53.493 --> 01:50:55.688
(TV) On first down,
the handoff is to Jones.

01:50:55.762 --> 01:50:58.822
He's on the right side.
He's got a blocker. And a first down.

01:50:58.899 --> 01:51:01.197
- But he's dropped inbounds.
- Nice.

01:51:01.268 --> 01:51:04.169
I guess Brandon was homesick.
I don't know.

01:51:04.237 --> 01:51:07.070
Or maybe he had
such deep feelings for me

01:51:07.140 --> 01:51:11.304
that he couldn't face saying goodbye.

01:51:15.882 --> 01:51:17.873
Wait a minute.

01:51:19.786 --> 01:51:22.721
I just got an idea. Just came to me.

01:51:22.789 --> 01:51:25.383
I mean, out of the blue.

01:51:25.459 --> 01:51:27.450
What about this?

01:51:28.328 --> 01:51:33.163
Brandon didn't tell me
he was gonna leave because...

01:51:34.167 --> 01:51:36.829
you let him fuck you.

01:51:38.872 --> 01:51:42.808
Back to pass, rolls under the left side.
Guns it over the middle, it's complete.

01:51:42.876 --> 01:51:45.640
Edwards has it, all the way
down to the 44, Kansas City.

01:51:45.712 --> 01:51:47.839
Oh, God.

01:51:48.448 --> 01:51:51.008
- You deny it?
- (whispers) Oh, my God.

01:51:52.386 --> 01:51:54.445
Do I have to, Walter?

01:51:54.521 --> 01:51:56.682
You know you did.

01:51:56.757 --> 01:51:59.123
Oh, you...
Another lock of the year?

01:51:59.192 --> 01:52:01.160
I saw you, Toni.

01:52:01.228 --> 01:52:04.129
I saw you and him, that night.

01:52:04.197 --> 01:52:06.597
I never went to Vegas.

01:52:06.666 --> 01:52:09.134
You mean you lied to me about the trip.

01:52:09.202 --> 01:52:11.397
Oh, don't talk to me about lying.

01:52:11.471 --> 01:52:15.567
- I guess you had the whole thing set up.
- Oh, don't make this about me.

01:52:15.642 --> 01:52:19.942
- Just put me out there on a tray?
- I put a tray out there.

01:52:20.013 --> 01:52:25.076
You didn't have to shove a fucking apple
in your mouth and sit on it!

01:52:25.152 --> 01:52:28.986
He's looking for his hot receiver.
Edwards, again, got it! Kansas City, 23.

01:52:29.056 --> 01:52:30.785
Admit it!

01:52:31.625 --> 01:52:33.456
You played me, Walter.

01:52:33.527 --> 01:52:36.621
You're fucking-A I did.

01:52:37.431 --> 01:52:40.628
It worked. Didn't it?

01:52:40.700 --> 01:52:44.295
(TV) With eight seconds left, New York
has to spend their final time-out.

01:52:44.371 --> 01:52:46.601
Brandon was right.

01:52:46.673 --> 01:52:50.336
- But you don't deny it?
- It's the best pick he ever made.

01:52:51.244 --> 01:52:53.542
I don't know what that means.

01:52:53.613 --> 01:52:58.448
Deep drop sets up in the pocket. Fires
over the middle. Batted down at the line!

01:52:58.518 --> 01:53:02.716
So after everything,
it all comes down to one final play.

01:53:04.891 --> 01:53:08.884
You were gambling with me that night, Walter.
With me!

01:53:10.197 --> 01:53:12.495
Brandon knew it,
because he knew you.

01:53:12.566 --> 01:53:15.057
He told me he was sure
you were watching somehow.

01:53:15.135 --> 01:53:19.196
So he asked me in to spend the night
and put on a little show for you, Walter.

01:53:19.272 --> 01:53:23.265
But I didn't believe him, Walter.
Oh, God, I didn't believe him.

01:53:23.343 --> 01:53:27.143
I mean, after all we've been through.
So I figured, you know, "What the hell?"

01:53:27.214 --> 01:53:29.774
He slipped out the back, no big deal.

01:53:29.850 --> 01:53:32.250
He never even stayed here.

01:53:32.752 --> 01:53:34.310
And you.

01:53:34.387 --> 01:53:37.220
You were in such a good mood
the next day.

01:53:37.290 --> 01:53:39.884
I figured, "Thank God,
because he must've been wrong."

01:53:39.960 --> 01:53:43.361
"Otherwise, why wouldn't he confront us,
confront me?"

01:53:43.430 --> 01:53:44.897
Oh, Walter.

01:53:44.965 --> 01:53:49.868
So it all boils down to this.
Can New York find the end zone?

01:53:49.936 --> 01:53:52.530
This is what players dream of.

01:53:52.606 --> 01:53:56.167
The chance to win it on the final snap.

01:53:56.243 --> 01:54:00.737
You wanted to lose! Like I was something
you could just toss on the table!

01:54:00.814 --> 01:54:03.374
Only we booked your bet, Walter,
Brandon and me,

01:54:03.450 --> 01:54:07.284
who evidently love you
more than you love yourself.

01:54:08.655 --> 01:54:11.283
Spreads the defense.
Drops back to throw.

01:54:11.358 --> 01:54:14.020
Here comes the pressure.
He bounces to the right side.

01:54:14.094 --> 01:54:17.427
Your fantasy is to end up alone
with nothing!

01:54:19.432 --> 01:54:21.423
I won't let that happen.
Understand?

01:54:21.501 --> 01:54:24.299
I will never let that happen to you.
This is it.

01:54:24.371 --> 01:54:27.534
He's on the run,
picks up a big block downfield.

01:54:27.607 --> 01:54:32.601
This is real, Walter.
You and me and Julia, we're all that's real.

01:54:34.548 --> 01:54:35.913
One man to beat.

01:54:36.616 --> 01:54:39.050
This is it, Walter.

01:54:39.119 --> 01:54:41.212
He goes airborne from the five.

01:54:41.288 --> 01:54:43.586
- Does he get in?
- He's in! He's in!

01:54:45.125 --> 01:54:47.958
Touchdown, New York!

01:54:55.168 --> 01:54:57.659
(conversation muted by music)

